==English==

===Etymology===
1800s usage, probably from the imagery that eggshells are easily broken when stepped upon.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|Received Pronunciation}} {{IPA|en|/ˌwɔːk ɒn ˈɛɡʃɛlz/}}
* {{a|General American}} {{IPA|en|/ˌwɔk ɑn ˈɛɡʃɛlz/|/ˌwɑk-/|/-ɔn-/}}
* {{audio|en|En-au-walk on eggshells.ogg|Audio (AU)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|*}}

# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} To be overly [[careful]] in dealing with a person or situation because they get [[angry]] or [[offended]] very easily; to try very hard not to [[upset]] someone or something.
# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} To be careful and [[sensitive]], in handling very sensitive matters.

